I recently tried the samosa chaat, aloo paratha and chicken cheese paratha and it was absolutely divine! address: 124 Streatham High Rd, London SW16 1BW, United Kingdom
name: Nabs
text:
I recently had the pleasure of dining at Paratha Inn Streatham and was thoroughly impressed with the food, customer service, and atmosphere. I tried the chicken and cheese paratha, karak tea, and cheesecake, and everything was absolutely delicious. The paratha was perfectly cooked.
The chicken and cheese filling was flavorful and well-seasoned.
The karak tea was aromatic and refreshing, and the cheesecake was creamy and decadent. 👌

In addition to the delicious food, the customer service at Paratha Inn was impeccable. 🤗 The staff was friendly, attentive, and knowledgeable about the menu. They made sure that we had everything we needed and that our dining experience was enjoyable.

The atmosphere of Paratha Inn was warm and inviting. The restaurant was decorated in a traditional Pakistani style, with comfortable seating and soft lighting. The overall ambiance was perfect for a relaxing meal with friends or family.❤️

I highly recommend Paratha Inn to anyone looking for a delicious and authentic Pakistani/Indian dining experience. I will definitely be visiting again soon!

text:
It looks like a nice place and seems clean. My friend ordered a plain paratha with omelette and shami keba. However she asked for a bigger omelette and said she would pay more. Instead they just didn’t give her kebab. And zero apology, instead he said that was her order, instead of the kebab. There was a clear misunderstanding but he do anything about it.

- the plain paratha was so hard not how it should be. We informed Dhruv at the restaurant and they did nothing to rectify the issue, not even replace it. I did say this was poor service and most restaurants would take it off the bill but instead he took off £1! What an insult! Again I pointed out that they should remove that from the bill as she only managed to eat a quarter. He then said I can top up your mango lasi by half of her small cup!!!! Really!!!

- I ordered a chicken and cheese naan and this was delicious. However I will not go there again based on the service and very hard paratha and which they did zero to sort out!!

name: The Boss
text:
Was really looking forward to some great food here.
Far B off the mark. If your name is pranthaa it should be the best around sadly had a much better one elsewhere
Pranthaa was too crispy, crunchy, bland, and flavourless. Because they use exclusively white flour it’s far too rich.  Omelette was ok but too oily. Reshmi kebab was disgusting and undercook to the point of being raw mush.

Flagged to the staff and they said it’s like that. So I guess food poisoning is part of the joint.

Found a random hair hiding under the other Pranthaa (also not very great) we ordered. Staff apologised and offered us a replacement but we didn’t want to eat anything else from here

Chai was spot on. Sadly not enough to carry this review especially when it’s name is about the Pranthaa.

name: Vivek Patel
text: I visited this place today to try it out as it had just newly opened. I wasn’t sure what to expect, being Indian I had quite high expectations. I was not disappointed at all. I ordered the chicken tikka roll. The paratha (wrap) was warm, crisply and flaky and soft all at the same time, there were generous amounts of chicken tikka pieces which were full of flavour and cooked to perfection. The salad in the wrap was crispy and fresh. The sauce in the wrap complimented the tikka and salad along with the paratha really well. I certainly will visit again, next time I want to try the paneer roll!
title: Paratha Inn (Streatham)

address: 124 Streatham High Rd, London SW16 1BW, United Kingdom
name: Rizo 323
text:
We visited Paratha Inn family of 5 today. Had a variety of food which was mostly nice. However the service was pretty poor. The food was served piecemeal and there was around a 10-15 minutes gap between first part of the order and last part being served. When I pointed this out I was told I should have requested the food be served together?? How very strange. The person serving did apologise but didn't take responsibility for poor service and why turn this around and put the onus on the customer? We were the only people there at the time which makes it even more strange why they can't cope with serving everyone at once.

So beware if there are more than two of you...ask for the food to be served together.

Better customer service and some humility goes a long way to repeat business!
